WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:09.780
[Amit Varma]: What is India's population? If you Google it, the number you will get is just over 1.3

00:00:09.780 --> 00:00:15.160
[Amit Varma]: billion people. But is that the real number? Think of it this way. Almost half of that

00:00:15.160 --> 00:00:20.300
[Amit Varma]: number is women. And in our country, women are treated as second class citizens. In most

00:00:20.300 --> 00:00:25.920
[Amit Varma]: of India, it's understood that a woman's destiny is to one day get married and raise a family.

00:00:25.920 --> 00:00:30.600
[Amit Varma]: The education of women, the education of girls rather, or their skilling, is not given enough

00:00:30.600 --> 00:00:35.480
[Amit Varma]: importance. And if they do ever end up getting into the workforce, they are already at a

00:00:35.480 --> 00:00:41.580
[Amit Varma]: huge disadvantage. Simply put, half the productive resources of our country are not treated as

00:00:41.580 --> 00:00:46.520
[Amit Varma]: productive resources at all. In fact, all our citizens are condescended to and restrained

00:00:46.520 --> 00:00:51.240
[Amit Varma]: by a parasitic Maybab government. And whatever we achieve as a society is in spite of the

00:00:51.240 --> 00:00:56.120
[Amit Varma]: state. But leave that aside for the moment. My point is that because of the way we treat

00:00:56.120 --> 00:01:02.080
[Amit Varma]: our women, we are functioning at any given point in time, at just half our capacity,

00:01:02.080 --> 00:01:07.840
[Amit Varma]: at best. And this is not just a function of our cultural norms. This is embedded in the

