00:07:48.600 --> 00:07:53.160
[Amit Varma]: have made clear that there are no exceptions at all to the values in the Constitution,

00:07:53.160 --> 00:07:57.780
[Amit Varma]: whatever religious practices any of our religions might have, if they go against the principles

00:07:57.780 --> 00:08:01.960
[Amit Varma]: we outlined in the Constitution, then they're unlawful period, right?

00:08:01.960 --> 00:08:08.080
[Guest 2]: So, that would be an idealistic and the preferable way of interpreting it, but that is unfortunately

00:08:08.080 --> 00:08:12.280
[Guest 2]: not the current legal position in practice.

00:08:12.280 --> 00:08:18.160
[Guest 1]: Okay, so the judiciary basically passed the buck onto the parliament, right?

00:08:18.160 --> 00:08:24.440
[Guest 2]: Yeah, meaning they said that while they've pronounced on this, nothing prevents the parliament

00:08:24.440 --> 00:08:25.840
[Guest 1]: from passing a law.

00:08:25.840 --> 00:08:27.720
[Guest 2]: Okay, so what did the parliament then do?

00:08:27.720 --> 00:08:37.360
[Guest 2]: So the parliament saw this as a clear opportunity, perhaps to reap political benefits, I don't

00:08:37.360 --> 00:08:42.840
[Guest 2]: know, but they passed a triple talaq bill, as it is colloquially known, the actual title

00:08:42.840 --> 00:08:46.440
[Guest 2]: is the Muslim Women Protection of Rights on Marriage Bill.

00:08:46.440 --> 00:08:51.720
[Guest 2]: Okay, so judging by that title, you would think that they deal with not only triple

00:08:51.720 --> 00:08:57.600
[Guest 2]: talaq, but all the various issues that Muslim women and Muslim women groups have been talking

00:08:57.600 --> 00:09:02.600
[Guest 2]: about for a while, like polygamy or nikkah halala.

00:09:02.600 --> 00:09:05.880
[Guest 2]: But there's no mention of those practices at all.

